<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id6c8ddad4-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e" identifier="/us/usc/t33/s3851"><num value="3851">§ 3851.</num><heading> Criminal enforcement</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Any person who knowingly violates paragraph (2), (3), (4), or (5) of <ref href="/us/usc/t33/s3841/a">section 3841(a) of this title</ref> or <ref href="/us/usc/t33/s3841/b">section 3841(b) of this title</ref> shall be fined under title 18 or imprisoned not more than 6 years, or both.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id6c8ddad5-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e">(<ref href="/us/pl/111/281/tX/s1041">Pub. L. 111–281, title X, § 1041</ref>, <date date="2010-10-15">Oct. 15, 2010</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/124/3029">124 Stat. 3029</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
